  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Portfolio Data**\n\nI\'m digging into the `portfolioData` now, particularly focusing on those tags such as \"B2B/Enterprise.\" My attention has shifted to `Home.tsx`, specifically lines 94-124, where I\'m re-examining how these tags are integrated and utilized. I\'m aiming to understand the construction logic there.\n\n\n**Clarifying Tag Rendering**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the tag rendering logic, specifically how the \" / \" separator is used. The goal is now to discern the user\'s intent when multiple tags are present, like in \"ERP / B2B\". My focus is on achieving a layout for tags. I want to build a design that uses `px 12, py 4, gap 4` with a background color that is similar to sticky headers.\n\n\n**Refining Tag Display Logic**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on handling multiple tags. The goal is now to discern the user\'s intent when multiple tags are present, like in \"ERP / B2B\". My focus is on achieving a layout for tags. I want to build a design that uses `px 12, py 4, gap 4` with a background color that is similar to sticky headers. I\'m now exploring using a flex container with inline tags, separated by slashes. I want a clean helper to parse the tags too. I am considering the nuances of \"if more than two\" (in Russian) meaning \"if multiple.\"\n\n\n**Implementing Tag Separation**\n\nI\'m now implementing the tag separation logic based on the user\'s input.  I\'m focusing on the \" / \" separator when multiple tags exist, and the design using `px 12, py 4, gap 4` with a sticky-header-like background. The latest structure includes a fragment for tags. I\'m building it as a container with separators between tags.\n\n\n**Revising Tag Structure**\n\nI\'m now questioning whether the flex container *holds* the tags or if the tag itself encapsulates the multiple values. I\'m reviewing the tag extraction logic, particularly the `getTags` function, which now splits the raw tags, trims, and uppercases. I\'m also examining the rendering with separators. My immediate focus is on ensuring each tag element has appropriate `px 12, py 4` padding.\n\n\n**Defining Tag Style**\n\nI\'m now clarifying the visual style of the tags, focusing on the padding, font size, and semi-transparent background with blur, mirroring sticky header aesthetics. I am deciding how to apply the layout using `px 12, py 4, gap 4` to tag elements and their separator. I\'m considering if individual tags, each with their own padding, are inside a flex container. I want to use `gap: var(--spacing-component-px-2xs)` within the container.\n\n\n**Structuring Tag Elements**\n\nI\'m now determining how to render multiple tags with a slash separator, considering whether the separator itself is a pill or plain text between individual tag pills. My focus is on the `work-card__tags-container`, which has absolute positioning, and a 4px gap. Each tag, the `work-card__tag`, will have a specific font style and size.\n\n\n**Styling Tag Components**\n\nI\'m now styling the tags with specific CSS properties. I\'ve set the background color, added blur, and defined padding and border-radius to match the sticky header. The box-shadow is added for depth. I\'m styling the separator, including color, font and opacity. I now have the design to support any number of tags!\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 11
      nanos: 886246368
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
