  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Width Constraints**\n\nI\'ve homed in on `.work-card__tags-container` as the target for width adjustments. It looks like implementing `min-width: 240px;` and `max-width: 480px;` is the correct approach to refine its responsiveness. I am confident in this direction and plan to incorporate it right away.\n\n\n**Refining Layout and Alignment**\n\nI\'ve decided to add `justify-content: center` to the `.work-card__tags-container` in `/src/styles/components/work-card.css`. This is to ensure the tags center gracefully when the container expands, creating an elegant horizontal bar. I\'m keen on seeing how this aligns visually; it should refine the tag presentation when the container\'s width exceeds its contents.\n\n\n"
